{"serial": "33006", "department_serial": 31, "code": "ME1055", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Introduction to Opto-Mechatronic Engineering", "ch": "光機電工程概論"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Chih-Yang Lin"], "ch": ["林智揚"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["5", "6"]}, "loc": {"building": "E2", "room": "410"}}], "isRequired": true, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 60, "department": {"ch": "機械工程學系", "en": "Department of Mechanical Engineering"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 4, "selected": 60, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程教學重點包含：智慧機器人、先進載具、光機電設備 等三大面向。光機電領域老師將聯合授課分別就三大面向的特定技術或系統進行概述，並針對部分關鍵技術進行探討與分析。以期能讓大一的光機電組學生能對光機電工程技術與系統有基本的認識與瞭解，並可作為培養學生成為光機電工程的研發、設計、實作與產業實務等人才之基礎學科。另可提供學生未來在修課、選定專長領域與生涯規劃方面之評估與參考的知識。", "en": "The key teaching focus of this course includes three major aspects: intelligent robots, advanced vehicles, and optomechatronic equipment. Instructors from the optomechatronics field will jointly teach, providing an overview of specific technologies or systems related to these three aspects, and discussing and analyzing some critical technologies. The aim is for first-year optomechatronics students to gain a basic understanding of optomechatronics engineering technologies and systems. This foundation will help in developing students into talent capable of R＆D, design, implementation, and practical industry applications in optomechatronics engineering. Additionally, it will provide knowledge for students to evaluate and reference in future course selection, specialization fields, and career planning."}, "outline": {"ch": "第1週 課程簡介、簡報製作原則。\n第2-6週 光機電設備：光機電工程概念簡介、 顯示技術、太陽能系統、半導體設備及主題成果評量。\n7-11 智慧機器人：自動光學檢測設備、機器人簡介、機器人實作、機器人感測技術及 主題成果評量。\n第12-17週 先進載具：自駕車概論、多重感測導航與定位、電腦視覺、先進載具相關實作與競賽介紹及主題成果評量。\n第18週 自主學習與期末報告修正", "en": "Week 1: Course introduction and principles of presentation preparation.\nWeeks 2-6: Optomechatronic Equipment: Introduction to optomechatronic engineering concepts, display technology, solar energy systems, semiconductor equipment, and evaluation of thematic projects.\nWeeks 7-11: Intelligent Robots: Automated optical inspection equipment, introduction to robots, robot implementation, robot sensing technology, and evaluation of thematic projects.\nWeeks 12-17: Advanced Vehicles: Introduction to self-driving cars, multi-sensor navigation and positioning, computer vision, practical work related to advanced vehicles, introduction to competitions, and evaluation of thematic projects.\nWeek 18: Self-directed study and final report revisions."}, "textbook": {"ch": "教師自編講義", "en": "None"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100", "en": "100"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "單元作業與心得報告30％、期末專題報告60％以及平常成績(平時出席與課堂表現)10％", "en": "Unit assignments and reflection reports: 30％, final project report: 60％, and regular performance (attendance and classroom participation): 10％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期一下午", "en": "Monday afternoon"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "17+1", "en": "17+1"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "將安排自主學習等學習活動，將進行最後期末報告修正", "en": "Self-directed study and other learning activities will be arranged, followed by the revisions of the final report."}, "domain": {"ch": "基礎學科", "en": "基礎學科"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "專業知識與技能", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "工程設計與整合", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試"]}, {"competencies": "專業倫理與社會責任", "rating": "(2)低", "assesments": ["口頭報告/口試"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Engineering Knowledge and Problem Analysis", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam"]}, {"competencies": "Design / Development of Solution and Investigation", "rating": "(4)High", "assesments": ["Presentation/Oral Exam"]}, {"competencies": "The Engineer and Society", "rating": "(2)Low", "assesments": ["Presentation/